lliurex-auto-upgrade (0.33) noble; urgency=medium

   * Improved Unattended Upgrades Management:
    - Set the APT cache directory to a custom path
      (/var/cache/lliurex-auto-upgrade/archives).
    - Replaced time.sleep with wakeup_event when waiting for dpkg processes
      to finish, improving overall application responsiveness.
    - Fixed a missing .clear() on the wakeup_event loop.
    - Enhanced security validation: handled cases where check_certificate returns
      unexpected values by allowing lliurex-auto-upgrade to automatically upgrade
      itself prior to throwing an exception.
    - Optimized error handling: reduced apt-mark terminal outputs during unattended
      installations and trimmed failure exception messages to display only the last
      20 lines of the output.
    - Mitigated potential process deadlocks by switching subprocess.Popen streams
      to use stdout=subprocess.PIPE and combining stderr into stdout.
  * Process Locking Fixes:
    - Migrated the PID file management to a more robust file-locking method
      using fcntl.flock to prevent multiple concurrent instances from running.
    - Fixed an incorrect file handle usage within the new fcntl implementation.
  * Code Quality & Bug Fixes:
    - Removed obsolete testing code, including simulated logic that skipped
      downloading the lliurex_actions.json file.
    - Cleaned up old Python file management logic by replacing manual open/close
      calls with 'with open(...)' context managers.
    - Fixed broken syntax in f-string print logs and optimized performance by
      breaking early out of the certificate organization identifier check loop
      once verified.

  * Missing release changes from 0.32
   - Added check-unattended-upgrades cli option to gather unattended upgrades
    information/state.
   - Improved print information to include package count.
   - Added remote server action override to allow svnlliurexnet to dinamically
     disable unattended upgrades.
   - Renamed 'linux' update category to 'kernel' and expanded kernel package
     filter
   - Package filter moved from being hardcoded to configuration-driven in
     /etc/lliurex-auto-upgrade/unattended_upgrade.conf
   - pprint method now allows calling with an empty default string.

 -- Hector Garcia Huerta <hectorgh@gmail.com>  Tue, 21 Jul 2026 10:16:20 +0200

